			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">RLE is good for lots of things, I think. For example, the overworld in Final Fantasy is probably more than 50% water. RLE compresses these rows to be two or so bytes instead of 140 in some spots.
<br />
<br />I made an RPG map scroller that loads an RLE compressed map like this. The major disadvantage with it is that it can take FOREVER to work through. The problem is that you have to go through every individual byte to get to the tile you want. There can be no calculating, as there's no way to tell what's compressed and what's not without checking every individual byte. It can take longer than a frame to get a column of metatiles depending on where you are in the map.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
