						<div class="postbody">For big maps that can be scrolled in any direction, recognizing long "runs" in one direction can be hard to deal with. Perhaps a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quadtree" class="postlink">quadtree subdivision</a> method like tokumaru's might help: if a node is entirely water, entirely grass, etc., we can replace it with one byte.</div>

